data.meta_description: Matt Maldonado (37) Kicker/Punter - 2023 Appeared in 10 games for the Racers. led the Racers in scoring with 41 points (7FG & 20 PAT). Was 20-of-20 in PATs. ...
data.text:
2023

Appeared in 10 games for the Racers.

led the Racers in scoring with 41 points (7FG & 20 PAT).

Was 20-of-20 in PATs.

Made 7-of-8 field goal attempts.

His career-long field goal was a 44-yard effort against Southern Illinois.

Had one kick off for 65 yards and a touchback.

Before MSU

In 2022, transferred to MSU from Wisconsin-Whitewater.

In his freshman season at UWW, earned All-Wisconsin Intercollegiate Athletic Conference honors.

Ranked 18th in NCAA Division III in field goal percentage (.750) and 26th in field goals per game (0.92).

Converted 53-of-57 extra points in 2021.

Kicked off 84 times for an average of 59 yards and 12 touchbacks.

Punted 24 times for an average of 37.58 yards.

His career-long field goal was 49 yards in 2021 against Wisc.-La Crosse.

Made another field goal of 45 yards against Wisc.-Eau Claire.

Competed in football, soccer and track and field at Yorkville High School.

Personal

Born Jan. 29, 2003, son of Alex and Alicia Maldonado.
